02:29.649 --> 02:31.241
<i>NARRATOR: Once upon a time,</i>

02:31.351 --> 02:33.478
<i>there was a brave little mouse</i>

02:33.553 --> 02:37.250
<i>who loved honor and justice</i>
<i>and always told the truth.</i>

02:37.924 --> 02:39.186
(CAPTAIN BARKING ORDERS)

02:51.838 --> 02:53.567
<i>No, that's not him.</i>

02:53.740 --> 02:54.764
(YAWNING)

02:55.275 --> 02:56.742
<i>That's a rat.</i>

02:57.076 --> 02:58.202
<i>And anyone who knows anything,</i>

02:58.278 --> 03:00.838
<i>knows there's a big difference</i>
<i>between a mouse and a rat.</i>

03:00.914 --> 03:01.938
Ohhh.

03:02.215 --> 03:05.007
<i>First of all,
rats hate the light.</i>

03:05.919 --> 03:07.045
(GROANS)

03:07.687 --> 03:10.281
<i>They spend their
lives in the darkness.</i>

03:10.623 --> 03:11.885
<i>They're also terrified of people,</i>

03:11.958 --> 03:14.085
<i>which is why they slink</i>
<i>and cower all the time.</i>

03:14.194 --> 03:15.218
Ooh!

03:15.562 --> 03:17.757
<i>And as far as telling
the truth is concerned,</i>

03:17.864 --> 03:20.628
<i>well, that's impossible</i>
<i>because, as everyone knows,</i>

03:20.900 --> 03:21.958
(CLEARS THROAT)

03:22.068 --> 03:23.797
<i>a rat can't talk.</i>

03:23.970 --> 03:25.460
Tell me that thing again, please.

03:25.939 --> 03:27.133
Come on.

03:27.807 --> 03:29.104
Just once, I promise.

03:29.209 --> 03:30.301
Tell me one more time,

03:30.410 --> 03:32.071
and I won't ask you ever again. I swear.

03:32.145 --> 03:33.237
(SIGHS)

03:33.313 --> 03:36.248
Fine. We are headed to Dor,

03:36.316 --> 03:39.114
one of the most
magical places in the whole world.

03:39.219 --> 03:40.743
No, that's not what you said before.

03:40.820 --> 03:43.380
You know, every place
has something special.

03:43.456 --> 03:45.924
And, in Dor, it's the soup!

03:46.059 --> 03:47.754
SAILOR: Land ho!

03:47.894 --> 03:49.759
(SAILORS CHEER)

03:51.965 --> 03:52.989
Ohhh.

03:54.167 --> 03:55.566
SAILOR 1: It's down below, I tell you.

03:55.635 --> 03:56.659
SAILOR 2: Give it a heave.

04:01.774 --> 04:03.241
I can see it!

04:05.678 --> 04:09.409
Ooh, I can smell it! I can smell it.

04:16.755 --> 04:19.281
ROSCURO: Oh, I can't wait
to taste the soup!

04:19.591 --> 04:21.082
Just stay close.

04:21.160 --> 04:22.422
We leave again at 6:00.

04:22.495 --> 04:25.328
You know, we ought to think
about staying here just a little longer.

04:25.431 --> 04:27.422
Don't even think about it.

04:27.700 --> 04:28.758
Remember Shanghai?

04:28.835 --> 04:30.427
Yeah, but this place is different.

04:30.837 --> 04:32.805
I mean, this is special.

04:35.341 --> 04:39.038
<i>NARRATOR: On any given day,</i>
<i>just one whiff from one of the soup shops</i>

04:39.145 --> 04:41.545
<i>was almost like
having a full meal.</i>

04:42.215 --> 04:45.150
<i>But on one very
special day every year,</i>

04:45.218 --> 04:48.187
<i>the kingdom of Dor</i>
<i>was magically transformed.</i>

04:48.288 --> 04:50.779
(CROWD CHEERING)

04:50.857 --> 04:52.848
<i>In Dor, Christmas was nothing.</i>

04:52.959 --> 04:54.517
<i>Well, they still celebrated it,</i>

04:54.627 --> 04:57.323
<i>but it was nothing
compared to Soup Day.</i>

05:02.368 --> 05:03.392
Watch it, watch it.

05:03.503 --> 05:05.368
Incoming potatoes!

05:05.471 --> 05:07.200
Hurry! Hurry! Excuse us.

05:07.307 --> 05:10.367
<i>Every Dorian, young and old,</i>
<i>would flock toward the castle</i>

05:10.476 --> 05:13.502
<i>because they knew that,
at that very moment,</i>

05:13.579 --> 05:16.207
<i>deep within the royal kitchens,</i>

05:16.316 --> 05:18.181
<i>a masterpiece was being created.</i>

05:18.251 --> 05:20.014
DELIVERY MAN: Potatoes coming up!

05:27.427 --> 05:28.485
COOK 1: Let's go!

05:28.561 --> 05:29.585
COOK 2: Don't forget the parsley!

05:29.896 --> 05:31.363
COOK 1: Make sure it's clean!

05:42.408 --> 05:44.569
<i>NARRATOR: Everyone knew</i>
<i>Chef Andre was a genius,</i>

05:44.677 --> 05:49.046
<i>but they got reminded of it</i>
<i>on the first Sunday of every spring.</i>

05:50.883 --> 05:53.215
<i>At exactly 12:00 noon,</i>

05:53.286 --> 05:56.722
<i>he would unveil that
year's royal creation.</i>

06:09.736 --> 06:10.862
More onions!

06:10.937 --> 06:11.961
More onions!

06:12.071 --> 06:13.095
More onions!

06:13.206 --> 06:14.264
More onions!

06:15.908 --> 06:17.876
<i>They would jam the town square,</i>

06:17.944 --> 06:20.242
<i>and, as the aroma began to build,</i>

06:20.313 --> 06:22.440
<i>so did their anticipation.</i>

06:25.084 --> 06:26.984
- Ohhh!
- Ow!

06:27.086 --> 06:28.110
Sorry.

06:28.221 --> 06:29.916
(TRUMPET FANFARE PLAYING)

06:29.989 --> 06:31.047
(CROWD CHEERING)

06:36.562 --> 06:37.620
Wow.

06:40.400 --> 06:41.458
Thank you.

06:41.567 --> 06:42.591
(CLEARS THROAT)

06:42.802 --> 06:47.637
It's my pleasure to announce
this year's royal creations

06:47.907 --> 06:50.205
from the kitchens of Chef Andre.

06:50.710 --> 06:51.972
Oh, no, no, no, no, no!

06:52.078 --> 06:53.545
Something is wrong.

06:53.613 --> 06:55.240
I need more time!

06:55.381 --> 06:56.609
But we're late already!

06:56.716 --> 06:58.308
This is not right!

07:00.453 --> 07:01.943
Everyone out!

07:02.388 --> 07:03.412
Out!

07:06.926 --> 07:10.555
<i>NARRATOR: Now, it's hard to</i>
<i>be a genius all by yourself.</i>

07:11.097 --> 07:14.897
<i>In fact, sometimes,
it takes a little help.</i>

07:38.291 --> 07:39.690
You changed something.

07:40.026 --> 07:42.119
You're crazy. I did not touch it.

07:42.195 --> 07:43.287
- I can smell it.
- Hmm?

07:43.362 --> 07:44.454
- What's this?
- What?

07:44.530 --> 07:46.157
- This!
- Ow! Garlic.

07:46.599 --> 07:47.759
- Garlic.
- Yeah, a little garlic.

07:48.367 --> 07:49.925
- It was already there.
- No.

07:50.002 --> 07:51.026
- Yes.
- No.

07:51.137 --> 07:52.195
- Yes.
- Not this much!

07:52.305 --> 07:53.329
Ow!

07:53.439 --> 07:54.531
You ruined my soup!

07:54.640 --> 07:56.039
I save your soup!

07:56.142 --> 08:01.136
Those people wait all year,
and you want to give them this dishwater.

08:01.881 --> 08:03.178
Dishwater?

08:03.282 --> 08:04.510
Dishwater.

08:04.617 --> 08:05.675
Dishwater?

08:05.785 --> 08:06.877
Ow! Cut it out!

08:07.019 --> 08:08.281
(CLAMORING)

08:09.689 --> 08:10.986
(CROWD CHEERING)

08:11.057 --> 08:12.820
And this year's soup is

08:14.861 --> 08:16.829
a spring tureen

08:16.896 --> 08:18.625
with a <i>mélange</i>
of roasted vegetables...

08:18.698 --> 08:19.722
Oh.

08:19.832 --> 08:21.561
...fresh herbs...
- Mmm!

08:21.667 --> 08:23.328
...and wild mushrooms.

08:23.402 --> 08:24.528
Oh.

08:25.204 --> 08:26.466
Roscuro?

08:30.643 --> 08:32.076
Roscuro?

08:32.712 --> 08:34.475
Oh. Evening.

08:38.484 --> 08:42.921
CHEF ANDRE: I don't have to stand here
and listen to a big talking garbage can!

08:43.089 --> 08:46.718
BOLDO: Ha! And I don't have
to stand here and listen to a coward!

08:47.026 --> 08:48.584
- Coward?
- Yes, a coward!

08:48.694 --> 08:50.525
- You call me coward?
- Yes!

08:50.596 --> 08:52.359
(SCREAMS)

08:52.932 --> 08:54.194
(GASPS)

08:54.600 --> 08:56.067
Oh, no!

09:03.943 --> 09:05.001
(EXCLAIMS)

09:07.513 --> 09:09.071
(BOLDO YELPS)

09:13.586 --> 09:15.076
Oh, no, no, no, no, no.

09:15.187 --> 09:16.745
(MUTTERING) That did it.

09:21.127 --> 09:22.890
- Hmm?
- Mmm.

09:23.296 --> 09:24.627
BOTH: Mmm!

09:24.964 --> 09:26.556
(CHUCKLES)

09:26.632 --> 09:28.862
<i>- Bellissima!</i>
- It's <i>fantastique!</i>

09:28.935 --> 09:31.904
Roscuro! Roscuro, where are you?

09:33.072 --> 09:34.596
(TRUMPET FANFARE PLAYING)

09:35.141 --> 09:36.267
Ohhh.

09:43.616 --> 09:44.878
(DRUM ROLLS)

09:48.588 --> 09:49.919
(ALL GASP)

09:55.494 --> 09:56.586
(SNIFFS)

09:56.662 --> 09:57.890
Whoa!

10:13.679 --> 10:14.805
(SNIFFS)

10:19.585 --> 10:20.745
<i>Voilà!</i>

10:21.020 --> 10:24.080
This is amazing!

10:24.323 --> 10:26.018
CHEF ANDRE: Wait till
Your Highness tastes it.

10:28.294 --> 10:29.318
Hmm?

10:41.173 --> 10:42.538
QUEEN: This is...

10:42.642 --> 10:43.666
Whoa!

10:43.776 --> 10:45.767
...absolutely...

10:45.845 --> 10:46.869
(EXCLAIMS)

10:46.979 --> 10:50.813
Oh, it moved! My soup moved!

10:50.983 --> 10:53.178
No, it isn't... It did not move.

10:53.853 --> 10:55.047
Oh, Your Highness.

10:55.154 --> 10:56.212
- Ahhh!
- Darling?

10:56.322 --> 10:59.314
Oh! A rat! There's a rat in my soup!

10:59.392 --> 11:01.019
Madam, I know that this is unfortunate.

11:01.127 --> 11:03.288
And I know that
while on first glance, I might...

11:03.362 --> 11:05.489
- A rat! In my soup!
- No. Please. Shh, shh, shh.

11:05.564 --> 11:07.657
- And I ate it!
- Your Highness, hold on...

11:07.733 --> 11:08.791
(GAGGING)

11:08.868 --> 11:10.665
- Uh-oh.
- She's right! It's a rat!

11:10.736 --> 11:11.828
(GASPS)

11:11.904 --> 11:13.963
- Please...
- Ahhh! It's a rat!

11:14.840 --> 11:17.866
Get me that rat!

11:18.210 --> 11:19.905
Now, I really believe
you're jumping to conclusions.

11:20.413 --> 11:21.903
And I'm sure that the
rats you met last time

11:22.014 --> 11:24.209
might have caused you
to create a stereotype,

11:24.316 --> 11:25.874
but... But I... But...

11:25.985 --> 11:28.215
It's just... I'm just...
I'm not really from around here.

11:28.320 --> 11:30.049
I'm... I'm from... Oh...

11:30.156 --> 11:31.214
Oh!

11:31.323 --> 11:32.756
That's very aggressive.

11:33.325 --> 11:34.383
GUARD: Get him!

11:34.493 --> 11:35.551
Kitchen...

11:35.661 --> 11:36.923
He's going into the kitchen!

11:39.265 --> 11:40.323
Oh!

11:45.237 --> 11:46.295
GUARD: Over there!

11:47.506 --> 11:49.133
Stop that rat!

11:49.909 --> 11:51.137
Whoa!

11:51.911 --> 11:52.969
GUARD: I got him!

11:53.045 --> 11:54.137
Uh-oh.

12:01.053 --> 12:03.715
He's going near the soup!

12:07.059 --> 12:08.083
GUARD: There he is!

12:08.260 --> 12:10.228
lf... If I could just tell...

12:10.696 --> 12:13.597
GUARD: On the kettle!
That's him, right there!

12:18.003 --> 12:19.027
Look, up there!

12:26.779 --> 12:27.837
(SIGHS)

12:29.281 --> 12:31.112
Sweetie? Darling?

12:32.551 --> 12:34.075
She's... She's...

12:35.588 --> 12:38.216
She's...

12:38.924 --> 12:41.586
Blimey, she's dead. Get him!

12:41.694 --> 12:43.423
GUARD: Don't let him escape!

12:43.529 --> 12:45.759
We'll get you, you rowdy rat!

12:47.366 --> 12:48.526
Oh!

12:52.538 --> 12:53.562
No, no, no!

12:53.639 --> 12:55.368
No, not there!

13:45.958 --> 13:47.983
(SOBBING)

13:57.036 --> 13:59.163
You don't need to be afraid.

14:00.372 --> 14:03.341
I know it's dark,
but you'll get used to it.

14:04.043 --> 14:05.840
Who... Who are you?

14:06.645 --> 14:08.943
Just a rat, like you.

14:10.616 --> 14:12.049
Come with me.

14:24.496 --> 14:28.330
<i>NARRATOR: When something hurts
this much, there must be a reason.</i>

14:29.201 --> 14:31.499
<i>There must be someone to blame.</i>

14:35.341 --> 14:36.535
(CLEARS THROAT)

14:37.977 --> 14:41.140
"From this moment on, soup,

14:41.213 --> 14:46.742
"the making of soup,
the selling of soup, or the eating of soup,

14:47.019 --> 14:50.182
"is hereby outlawed
in the kingdom of Dor!

14:58.197 --> 15:01.564
"Rats are to be
considered illegal as well

15:01.667 --> 15:06.331
"and are hereby deemed
unlawful creatures in the kingdom of Dor!

15:06.405 --> 15:07.702
"From this moment on,

15:07.773 --> 15:13.040
"anyone harboring, sheltering
or possessing a rat in any way,

15:13.112 --> 15:15.672
"shall face the full wrath of the law!"

15:17.016 --> 15:18.847
<i>NARRATOR: So think about this.</i>

15:18.918 --> 15:23.719
<i>What happens when you make something</i>
<i>illegal that is just a natural part of the world?</i>

15:25.524 --> 15:27.583
<i>You may as well
make flies illegal.</i>

15:27.693 --> 15:29.888
<i>Or sweat. Or Monday morning.</i>

15:30.796 --> 15:34.254
<i>But that's what the King did</i>
<i>out of a terrible sadness.</i>

15:38.470 --> 15:41.064
<i>Sunlight left and
the world went gray.</i>

15:42.408 --> 15:46.435
<i>Colors faded into each other and</i>
<i>dark clouds filled the sky.</i>

15:48.547 --> 15:52.643
<i>And for a long time,
it wouldn't rain.</i>

15:56.322 --> 16:02.283
<i>The clouds just stayed</i>
<i>and stayed and stayed.</i>

16:08.767 --> 16:10.496
(SIGHS)

16:12.604 --> 16:14.435
I wish it would rain.

16:15.174 --> 16:16.664
You and the whole world, madam.

16:17.643 --> 16:18.667
Ow!

16:18.777 --> 16:19.903
Oh, sorry, milady!

16:20.579 --> 16:23.104
Well, at least I can still feel that.

16:26.151 --> 16:30.178
Louise, do you think
there's a bit of light

16:30.856 --> 16:31.982
somewhere in the world?

16:32.524 --> 16:33.616
Don't know, ma'am.

16:33.692 --> 16:35.319
I think there is.

16:36.261 --> 16:38.923
You just need to know where to find it.

16:51.076 --> 16:53.476
<i>NARRATOR: Okay, remember</i>
<i>when we told you how,</i>

16:53.579 --> 16:56.446
<i>once upon a time,</i>
<i>there was this brave little mouse?</i>

16:56.515 --> 17:00.076
<i>Well, if you know
anything about fairytales,</i>

17:00.152 --> 17:04.349
<i>you know that a
hero doesn't appear</i>

17:04.455 --> 17:06.753
<i>until the world really needs one.</i>

17:16.535 --> 17:18.162
(MICE SCREAMING)

17:20.705 --> 17:21.832
MOUSE: Oh, look out!

17:21.940 --> 17:25.137
Alms for the blind! Alms for the blind!

17:25.877 --> 17:26.935
(EXCLAIMS)

17:31.316 --> 17:32.374
(MICE CHATTERING)

18:03.348 --> 18:04.576
Excuse me. Excuse me.

18:05.184 --> 18:06.515
Excuse me.

18:06.985 --> 18:08.350
Excuse me.

18:09.088 --> 18:10.521
- Whoa!
- I'm sorry. Sorry.

18:10.589 --> 18:11.817
- Tilling?
- Oh!

18:12.191 --> 18:13.886
Mr. Mayor, hello!

18:13.992 --> 18:15.152
Where are you going?

18:15.227 --> 18:19.061
(STAMMERS) Oh, well,
my baby is having a...

18:19.164 --> 18:22.258
No, my wife is having a...

18:22.401 --> 18:24.494
Oh, right. Congratulations.

18:24.770 --> 18:26.101
Thank you. Thank you, sir.

18:26.705 --> 18:29.037
I'm sorry, I... I really... Goodbye.

18:38.050 --> 18:39.711
His eyes are open.

18:39.785 --> 18:41.184
Don't worry about it.

18:41.253 --> 18:42.948
Sometimes they are.

18:43.055 --> 18:44.579
But he isn't cowering.

18:44.690 --> 18:46.521
He's looking right at us.

18:46.592 --> 18:49.026
Don't worry. He'll learn to cower.

18:49.461 --> 18:51.224
They all do in time.

18:52.131 --> 18:53.621
ANTOINETTE: But he isn't!

19:00.472 --> 19:04.772
Wow! He's so puny!
And look at those ears!

19:05.777 --> 19:07.244
<i>NARRATOR: And,
from the very beginning,</i>

19:07.312 --> 19:09.542
<i>Despereaux Tilling heard more,</i>

19:09.615 --> 19:13.415
<i>saw more and even smelled more</i>
<i>than any of the other mice.</i>

19:19.224 --> 19:21.158
Despereaux, don't do it.

19:30.002 --> 19:31.060
(GASP)

19:32.404 --> 19:33.598
MOUSE 1: Don't look. Don't look!

19:33.672 --> 19:34.764
MOUSE 2: I won't, I won't.

19:35.908 --> 19:36.966
(GROANS)

19:42.948 --> 19:43.972
Mmm.

19:44.616 --> 19:47.483
<i>NARRATOR: Despereaux Tilling</i>
<i>had no idea he was small.</i>

19:48.587 --> 19:51.112
<i>He wasn't just small
in human terms.</i>

19:51.290 --> 19:53.758
<i>He was small even for a mouse.</i>

19:54.493 --> 19:57.587
<i>But, to tell you the truth,</i>
<i>he didn't even notice.</i>

19:57.863 --> 20:02.163
<i>In fact, in his own mind,</i>
<i>Despereaux was a giant.</i>

20:12.010 --> 20:13.807
We're worried about him.

20:13.879 --> 20:15.972
He doesn't scurry. He doesn't cower.

20:16.048 --> 20:18.312
At first, we thought he would
grow out of it, but...

20:18.383 --> 20:20.317
Well, he scurries sometimes.

20:20.385 --> 20:21.716
But not when he's scared!

20:21.820 --> 20:22.844
He just does it for fun.

20:22.955 --> 20:24.479
And he never cowers.

20:24.556 --> 20:25.682
We've showed him how, but he...

20:25.791 --> 20:28.282
Well, some kids are slower than others.

20:28.360 --> 20:30.487
He'll cower in time. We'll work on it.

20:30.562 --> 20:33.122
- Yes, but...
- It'll be fine, I promise.

20:33.832 --> 20:35.732
All right, settle down.

20:36.335 --> 20:37.802
Ready, class?

20:41.873 --> 20:42.897
(ALL GASP)

20:43.709 --> 20:44.835
Good.

20:47.179 --> 20:48.669
ALL: Mmm! Ah!

20:49.748 --> 20:51.340
Good. Excellent.

20:54.019 --> 20:56.146
(ALL SCREAM)

21:01.860 --> 21:04.192
- Despereaux!
- Yes?

21:04.263 --> 21:05.355
You didn't cower.

21:05.998 --> 21:07.022
Looks like a sword.

21:07.099 --> 21:09.590
It's a carving knife.

21:10.702 --> 21:12.897
It's beautiful!

21:13.005 --> 21:14.495
It's dangerous.

21:14.840 --> 21:16.831
Do you have anymore?

21:20.712 --> 21:22.703
Despereaux, what are you doing?

21:22.781 --> 21:24.271
We're not even supposed to be here.

21:24.383 --> 21:25.941
That's the dungeon.

21:26.051 --> 21:27.450
They have rats down there.

21:27.552 --> 21:29.042
And they'll eat you.

21:29.121 --> 21:31.021
And pull your arms off!

21:34.359 --> 21:36.054
How far down is it?

21:37.195 --> 21:39.561
I don't know. No one's ever come back.

21:39.631 --> 21:40.893
How come?

21:40.966 --> 21:42.433
'Cause... 'Cause...

21:42.601 --> 21:44.262
'Cause that's where
you go when you get...

21:44.369 --> 21:45.802
(STAMMERING) When you get...

21:45.904 --> 21:47.098
Banished.

21:48.106 --> 21:49.437
What do you get banished for?

21:49.741 --> 21:51.038
Oh, you know.

21:51.109 --> 21:52.371
- Rules and...
- Breaking.

21:52.477 --> 21:53.739
- We can't even...
- Talk about it...

21:53.812 --> 21:54.904
- Because...
- That's one of the...

21:55.580 --> 21:56.638
ALL: Rules!

21:59.418 --> 22:00.783
MOUSE 1: Despereaux!

22:02.421 --> 22:04.821
I just want to have a quick look.

22:05.057 --> 22:06.888
We got to get out of here!

22:08.960 --> 22:10.154
MOUSE 1: Oh, gosh.
MOUSE 2: Oh, no.

22:10.262 --> 22:11.388
ALL: Oh, jeez.

22:11.463 --> 22:12.623
Uh-oh.

22:27.412 --> 22:29.676
Despereaux! You can't feed them.

22:33.318 --> 22:34.785
Hello?

22:35.354 --> 22:38.915
(ECHOES)

22:40.826 --> 22:43.590
Here you go, whoever you are.

22:53.138 --> 22:54.264
(CHUCKLING) Nice.

23:28.240 --> 23:29.502
You are crazy!

23:29.574 --> 23:31.041
What I say? I said nothing!

23:31.143 --> 23:32.542
Well, you heard exactly what I said.

23:32.644 --> 23:34.202
- I say you crazy.
- No, no, no, no!

23:38.884 --> 23:40.647
(PLAYING MUSIC)

23:46.158 --> 23:47.887
(ALARM BELL RINGING)

23:50.529 --> 23:51.826
RAT: Hurry!

23:54.166 --> 23:55.758
(RATS CHANTING)

24:03.108 --> 24:05.338
(CROWD CHEERS)

24:05.410 --> 24:07.344
SMUDGE: Ha! They look hungry, sir.

24:07.412 --> 24:08.674
Mmm-hmm.

24:11.416 --> 24:12.781
Dinnertime.

24:14.719 --> 24:16.710
(CLAMORING)

24:19.724 --> 24:20.782
(CHUCKLES)

24:29.901 --> 24:31.528
You're not eating.

24:31.603 --> 24:33.969
Uh, I was.

24:34.072 --> 24:36.404
No, you weren't.

24:36.475 --> 24:39.911
Well, I'm just watching, sir.

24:40.378 --> 24:43.973
Well, that's not very grateful of you

24:44.082 --> 24:47.210
after I've taken you under my wing.

24:47.552 --> 24:51.921
(STAMMERING) Well, I'm grateful, really.
I am.

24:52.157 --> 24:54.091
You miss something, don't you?

24:54.159 --> 24:56.059
Uh, no, I don't.

24:56.228 --> 24:58.628
There's nothing up there, Roscuro.

24:59.231 --> 25:00.562
Nothing at all.

25:00.632 --> 25:03.100
Oh, no, I know that! Absolutely.

25:03.435 --> 25:06.029
Uh, nothing!

25:06.671 --> 25:08.662
Nothing. Nothing at all.

25:08.874 --> 25:10.364
He's a tough one.

25:10.475 --> 25:13.171
You're not gonna turn him.
Nah, you're not.

25:13.278 --> 25:17.806
Oh, I don't know. A rat is a rat.

25:18.316 --> 25:21.547
It doesn't really matter
where you come from.

25:51.383 --> 25:52.714
ROSCURO: I'm sorry.

26:04.763 --> 26:06.253
MOUSE: He is so weird.

26:06.431 --> 26:07.523
(LAUGHS) No kidding.

26:08.266 --> 26:10.234
That is so beautiful.

26:10.335 --> 26:11.666
I wonder what's out there.

26:30.522 --> 26:32.752
"February 1: Doesn't scurry.

26:32.857 --> 26:34.848
"February 3: Didn't cower.

26:34.926 --> 26:36.723
"Didn't cower. Didn't cower.

26:36.795 --> 26:38.262
"Wouldn't scurry."

26:38.363 --> 26:41.855
Oh, here's one:
"Drew pictures of cats on his notebook."

26:41.933 --> 26:43.958
- No! Cats?
- Oh! I can't imagine!

26:44.302 --> 26:47.465
I'm afraid so. Named it Fluffy.

26:48.106 --> 26:51.769
- Oh, I had no idea!
- Oh! That's terrible.

26:53.979 --> 26:55.776
- Despereaux.
- Yes, sir?

26:56.081 --> 26:57.378
Come in, please.

27:01.386 --> 27:03.377
Despereaux, why do you think
you're in school?

27:04.789 --> 27:05.915
To learn?

27:05.991 --> 27:07.083
- To learn, yes.
- Yes.

27:07.158 --> 27:08.216
To learn what?

27:09.394 --> 27:14.229
(HESITATING) To learn
how to be a mouse, sir.

27:14.666 --> 27:16.156
That is correct.

27:16.267 --> 27:18.667
And you can't be a mouse if
you don't learn to be afraid.

27:19.504 --> 27:21.233
Oh, Despereaux, this...

27:21.306 --> 27:24.275
There's so many
wonderful things in life to be afraid of

27:24.342 --> 27:26.242
if you'd just learn how scary they are.

27:26.411 --> 27:28.572
Yes. Yes, sir.

27:32.484 --> 27:33.746
How about his brother?

27:33.818 --> 27:35.149
His brother? What about him?

27:35.253 --> 27:38.188
Yes, is he, you know, timid?

27:38.823 --> 27:40.916
Oh! Oh, yes!

27:41.092 --> 27:42.753
- Yes, very timid.
- Yes. So timid!

27:42.827 --> 27:44.556
As timid as the day is long.

27:44.663 --> 27:45.994
Good. Good.

27:46.197 --> 27:48.859
Sometimes they just need
to see the older ones do it.

27:48.967 --> 27:50.491
No one starts out afraid.

27:50.869 --> 27:52.700
- Understood.
- Of course.

27:53.471 --> 27:54.995
- You coddle that boy, that's the problem.
- No.

27:55.073 --> 27:56.131
- Yes, you do.
- No, no.

27:56.207 --> 27:58.232
- Yes, you do. You've been doing it for years.
- He was always...

27:58.343 --> 27:59.367
He's little. I've had to help him.

27:59.477 --> 28:02.139
He's not going to be afraid unless
you allow him to be afraid.

28:02.213 --> 28:03.544
Well, Furlough will teach him.

28:09.854 --> 28:10.878
Do what he does.

28:10.989 --> 28:12.183
And don't do anything he doesn't.

28:12.257 --> 28:13.656
And if he's afraid of something...

28:13.725 --> 28:15.420
Then you need to be afraid of it, too.

28:36.347 --> 28:37.405
Oh!

28:42.253 --> 28:43.345
Wow.

28:56.935 --> 28:59.096
Come on, Furlough, hurry up!

29:03.108 --> 29:04.200
Whoa...

29:15.553 --> 29:18.420
FURLOUGH: All right, now, you start
nibbling right along that edge there.

29:19.257 --> 29:22.624
The glue is all right,
but it's the pages that taste the best.

29:23.294 --> 29:27.253
Hmm. "Once upon a time."
That's great, isn't it?

29:27.665 --> 29:29.155
"Upon a time."

29:29.334 --> 29:31.268
And they don't even tell you
what time that is yet.

29:31.336 --> 29:33.167
It's like you have to find that out.

29:33.271 --> 29:36.263
You're not supposed to read it, Despereaux.
You're supposed to eat it.

29:37.642 --> 29:39.940
Good. I'll come back in an hour.

29:41.112 --> 29:45.481
And no reading! It's a rule.

29:59.164 --> 30:02.930
<i>NARRATOR: Once upon a time,</i>
<i>there lived a fair princess,</i>

30:03.935 --> 30:06.335
<i>fairer than any in any other land.</i>

30:07.639 --> 30:09.300
Hmm. Fair.

30:10.141 --> 30:15.101
<i>And, as the story goes,</i>
<i>she was locked up in a faraway castle,</i>

30:15.213 --> 30:18.671
<i>where she could see the world</i>
<i>but could never touch it.</i>

30:21.519 --> 30:23.487
<i>She longed for a prince.</i>

30:24.322 --> 30:27.416
<i>A brave knight who would</i>
<i>deliver her from all of this.</i>

30:27.525 --> 30:31.427
<i>Someone with courage</i>
<i>and honor and decency.</i>

30:37.435 --> 30:39.562
<i>But in a cruel and
frightened world,</i>

30:39.671 --> 30:41.730
<i>men like this were scarce indeed.</i>

30:42.607 --> 30:43.665
(DRAGON ROARING)

30:45.210 --> 30:46.234
(GRUNTS)

31:23.615 --> 31:25.845
<i>They lived in a special world</i>

31:26.351 --> 31:29.809
<i>built on courage and
chivalry and honor.</i>

31:30.088 --> 31:32.249
<i>They pledged their
lives to each other.</i>

31:32.690 --> 31:35.989
<i>To fight for truth,
to defend the weak,</i>

31:36.094 --> 31:39.825
<i>to seek justice, and to always...</i>

31:44.502 --> 31:45.867
LESTER: How was the library?

31:45.970 --> 31:47.028
Fine.

31:47.605 --> 31:49.334
Spoil your appetite?

31:49.674 --> 31:51.938
No. Helped it, actually.

31:52.543 --> 31:54.170
Made me hungrier.

31:55.713 --> 31:56.975
Good lad.

32:00.051 --> 32:01.450
Ha-hah!

32:03.888 --> 32:07.380
Did you see they're putting up
a new front on the crumb shop?

32:07.492 --> 32:10.120
ANTOINETTE: Oh! But I loved the old front.
LESTER: Quite modern. Yes.

32:16.968 --> 32:19.163
<i>NARRATOR: Did a book
ever speak to you?</i>

32:19.504 --> 32:21.972
<i>Almost like it was
written for you?</i>

32:22.674 --> 32:24.642
<i>Despereaux loved it all.</i>

32:25.009 --> 32:26.636
<i>Every bit of it.</i>

32:26.811 --> 32:30.178
<i>The truth, the justice,
the bravery,</i>

32:30.515 --> 32:32.244
<i>the sword-fighting.</i>

32:34.319 --> 32:37.152
<i>He even loved things
you wouldn't suspect.</i>

32:38.189 --> 32:40.521
<i>The story said she was a prisoner,</i>

32:40.591 --> 32:42.752
<i>but that wasn't totally true</i>

32:42.894 --> 32:46.830
<i>because she had hope,</i>
<i>and whenever you have hope,</i>

32:46.898 --> 32:49.059
<i>you're never really
anybody's prisoner.</i>

32:49.701 --> 32:51.828
Someday, my prince will come.

32:52.437 --> 32:54.496
<i>But how did she know that?</i>

32:54.739 --> 32:56.866
Yeah, how did she know that?

32:58.943 --> 33:00.934
(LUTE PLAYING)

33:11.122 --> 33:12.180
(SNIFFLES)

33:24.769 --> 33:25.793
(GASPS)

33:38.649 --> 33:39.911
(PRINCESS PEA CRYING)

33:45.123 --> 33:46.590
DESPEREAUX: Why are you crying?

33:46.657 --> 33:47.681
(GASPS)

33:48.993 --> 33:50.790
Why are you crying?

33:52.296 --> 33:53.923
Down here.

33:54.198 --> 33:55.529
(GASPS) Are you a rat?

33:55.933 --> 33:56.957
No.

33:57.035 --> 33:58.696
What are you? A mouse?

34:01.672 --> 34:03.139
I am a gentleman.

34:04.108 --> 34:05.132
(CHUCKLES)

34:06.110 --> 34:07.634
And how do you do?

34:10.114 --> 34:11.138
You're sad.

34:11.983 --> 34:13.041
Yes.

34:13.351 --> 34:14.443
Because you have longing.

34:16.687 --> 34:18.177
You're a strange little mouse.

34:18.989 --> 34:20.014
Thank you.

34:23.728 --> 34:24.989
Come on.

34:33.071 --> 34:34.469
Where did you hear that?

34:35.373 --> 34:36.965
About the longing.

34:37.041 --> 34:38.371
In a story.

34:38.476 --> 34:40.501
A story? About what?

34:40.978 --> 34:43.708
About a princess, like you,
in a castle, like this.

34:44.849 --> 34:47.750
Oh. You're a smooth little mouse,
aren't you?

34:49.020 --> 34:51.487
Bet you tell that to all the princesses.

34:51.889 --> 34:53.719
I am sworn to tell the truth.

34:53.991 --> 34:55.424
It is a code of honor.

34:55.525 --> 35:00.259
Ah. Not just a gentleman,
an honorable gentleman.

35:01.732 --> 35:04.428
Well, then, how does this story end

35:04.535 --> 35:06.696
with this princess
who's locked in a castle?

35:06.771 --> 35:08.204
I don't know...

35:08.506 --> 35:10.030
I haven't finished it yet.

35:11.109 --> 35:12.508
I'd love to know.

35:13.544 --> 35:15.512
Oh, I wish it would rain.

35:15.947 --> 35:18.074
I wish there was soup again.

35:18.249 --> 35:20.376
I even wish there were rats!

35:21.552 --> 35:23.281
Will you promise me that?

35:23.387 --> 35:25.912
Will you promise to finish your story
and tell me how it ends?

35:26.457 --> 35:28.925
Yes. It will be my quest.

35:29.927 --> 35:33.294
Your quest! You are a very brave mouse.

35:39.704 --> 35:41.865
Thank you, my good gentleman.

35:48.146 --> 35:49.204
Whoa!

35:51.816 --> 35:52.942
Whoa.

35:57.989 --> 35:59.047
(EXCLAIMS)

36:02.460 --> 36:03.484
Whoa!

36:06.164 --> 36:07.256
(EXCLAIMS)

36:17.341 --> 36:20.674
<i>NARRATOR: Now, there are</i>
<i>all kinds of princesses.</i>

36:22.446 --> 36:24.346
<i>Some are born that way,</i>

36:24.448 --> 36:26.143
<i>some marry into it,</i>

36:26.350 --> 36:29.979
<i>and some are destined
to be princesses</i>

36:30.054 --> 36:31.487
<i>only in their own minds.</i>

36:33.191 --> 36:34.852
<i>But at one time or another,</i>

36:34.959 --> 36:37.985
<i>every little girl
longs to be a princess.</i>

36:40.298 --> 36:41.959
I'm gonna live right there.

36:42.066 --> 36:45.001
Right up there, near the tippy-top.

36:46.304 --> 36:49.637
Quit your daydreaming
and feed those swine!

36:50.341 --> 36:52.901
Yes, I know. It's gonna be all mine.

36:53.678 --> 36:58.581
No, you deaf little urchin.
I said feed those swine!

36:58.683 --> 36:59.707
(EARS RINGING)

37:02.320 --> 37:04.379
<i>NARRATOR: Miggery Sow had been</i>
<i>shoveling slop</i>

37:04.488 --> 37:06.547
<i>for as long as she could remember.</i>

37:06.757 --> 37:10.557
<i>Her Uncle Ned had put a shovel in her
hand from the minute she could hold one.</i>

37:11.362 --> 37:13.387
<i>But it turned out all right</i>

37:13.497 --> 37:15.488
<i>because she got on</i>
<i>quite nicely with the pigs.</i>

37:15.566 --> 37:17.033
That's right.

37:17.335 --> 37:21.237
I'm gonna have a special room
just for my dresses

37:21.505 --> 37:25.100
and another whole closet
just for my knickers!

37:25.243 --> 37:29.111
<i>In fact, Miggery Sow could</i>
<i>see her future so clearly.</i>

37:29.714 --> 37:33.878
<i>She could see the tiara, the fancy dresses,</i>
<i>the maids-in-waiting,</i>

37:34.552 --> 37:37.544
<i>and when things got</i>
<i>really bad around the farm,</i>

37:37.622 --> 37:42.025
<i>she could see the moment that she would
finally be delivered from all of this.</i>

37:42.460 --> 37:43.859
Not long now.

37:43.928 --> 37:45.623
I promise you that.

37:46.063 --> 37:50.727
20 for the big ones,
15 for the sow, and 12 for the girl.

37:51.202 --> 37:53.762
15 for the girl, same as the sow.

37:55.239 --> 37:58.868
I told you! I told you
I'd make it to the castle!

37:58.976 --> 38:00.466
Whoa!

38:02.113 --> 38:05.310
<i>So sometimes, it doesn't take much</i>
<i>for your dreams to come true.</i>

38:06.284 --> 38:09.151
<i>You just have to be
able to see it that way.</i>

38:09.954 --> 38:13.446
She was beautiful! Like an angel.

38:13.958 --> 38:15.619
FURLOUGH: You are crazy.

38:15.793 --> 38:18.455
And she smelled so amazing.

38:19.063 --> 38:20.223
Like a garden.

38:20.731 --> 38:21.755
Despereaux!

38:21.832 --> 38:23.823
You can't talk to a human.

38:23.934 --> 38:25.401
That is the worst thing you can do.

38:25.469 --> 38:27.403
No, it's the best thing I ever did.

38:27.571 --> 38:28.936
They will throw you in the dungeon.

38:29.006 --> 38:30.564
You will get eaten by rats!

38:30.641 --> 38:31.903
It would be worth it.

38:32.343 --> 38:34.311
They could tear at my flesh.

38:34.412 --> 38:35.777
Oh, this is bad.

38:35.846 --> 38:38.280
Oh, and when she held me
in her hand, it was...

38:38.849 --> 38:42.182
It was so soft,
like floating in a pillow.

38:42.553 --> 38:43.986
You know what? I'm worried about you.

38:44.322 --> 38:45.983
That's the point, Furlough.

38:46.057 --> 38:47.854
There's nothing to be afraid of.

38:47.958 --> 38:49.949
Quiet! They will hear you.

38:50.027 --> 38:51.790
Come on. Just try it.

38:52.063 --> 38:54.793
Just for a second, just try being brave.

38:54.965 --> 38:56.796
- Oh!
- And stop cowering!

38:56.901 --> 38:59.165
What's going on in here?

38:59.236 --> 39:03.900
What's all this talk
about princesses and bravery?

39:04.909 --> 39:07.537
Furlough, I want to see you
in my study, right now.

39:11.082 --> 39:13.312
LESTER: Are you sure?
FURLOUGH: That's what he said.

39:13.384 --> 39:15.818
- A real human?
- A princess.

39:15.886 --> 39:16.910
(SIGHS)

39:17.488 --> 39:18.580
We need to tell them.

39:18.689 --> 39:20.247
We need to tell the Mouse Council.

39:20.358 --> 39:22.656
- But they'll...
- This is bad. This is very bad.

39:22.727 --> 39:25.719
If they find out...
If they find out that they didn't find out...

39:25.830 --> 39:28.856
Oh, then they'll find
out that it was me who...

39:28.933 --> 39:30.025
Oh, no.

39:30.101 --> 39:32.262
But they will send him to the dungeon!

39:32.670 --> 39:35.230
- Oh, he'll get eaten by rats!
- Oh!

39:35.339 --> 39:36.829
No, not if we beg.

39:36.907 --> 39:40.934
If we really beg
and show them that he's changed.

39:41.345 --> 39:42.676
That he's afraid.

39:42.747 --> 39:46.239
That he's afraid,
and he's turned into a real mouse.

39:47.017 --> 39:48.382
Despereaux!

39:57.962 --> 40:00.522
<i>NARRATOR: Of course,</i>
<i>destiny is a funny thing.</i>

40:01.132 --> 40:04.761
<i>We go out to meet it,</i>
<i>and we don't always know that we are.</i>

40:14.311 --> 40:15.869
KNIGHT: For glory and honor!

40:15.980 --> 40:17.447
Surround him!

40:34.965 --> 40:36.262
MAYOR: Despereaux Tilling.

40:36.333 --> 40:37.391
(GASPS)

40:39.403 --> 40:42.270
How long have you been
working on this book?

40:42.339 --> 40:44.330
Hmm... A week?

40:44.442 --> 40:46.672
A week? You've hardly cracked it.

40:47.511 --> 40:49.001
Well, I was...

40:50.347 --> 40:52.144
I just wanted to see how it ends.

40:53.083 --> 40:55.313
(BELL TOLLS)

40:57.655 --> 40:58.917
(CROWD MURMURING)

41:02.860 --> 41:04.953
INQUISITOR: Refused training as a mouse.

41:05.029 --> 41:08.487
Refused to respect the will
and guidance of elder mice.

41:08.933 --> 41:12.596
Repeatedly engaged in bold
and un-meek behavior.

41:12.703 --> 41:17.697
Triggered willfully
not less than 17 mousetraps.

41:17.842 --> 41:18.866
(CROWD GASPS)

41:18.976 --> 41:20.034
Just shameful!

41:20.144 --> 41:22.339
Had personal contact with...

41:23.047 --> 41:24.071
With...

41:27.084 --> 41:28.210
With a human being.

41:28.319 --> 41:30.082
(CROWD MURMURING)

41:30.221 --> 41:32.348
Isn't there something you can do?

41:32.423 --> 41:34.482
Antoinette, stop right now! Stop that.

41:34.558 --> 41:36.025
You have to trust them.

41:36.093 --> 41:37.651
They are the Council.

41:37.728 --> 41:39.923
They're the Council because...

41:40.197 --> 41:42.722
Because they're the Council.

41:44.368 --> 41:45.835
They're the Council.

41:46.504 --> 41:48.233
Is there anything you wish to say
in your defense?

41:49.240 --> 41:53.006
Well, it was a very good story,

41:53.878 --> 41:57.370
and she was a very beautiful princess.

41:57.948 --> 41:59.415
(CROWD MURMURING)

42:00.117 --> 42:02.051
Despereaux Tilling,

42:02.119 --> 42:05.714
our laws are here
to protect us and our way of life.

42:06.357 --> 42:09.884
And when one of our citizens
strays from that way of life,

42:10.261 --> 42:12.525
he becomes a threat to us all.

42:13.130 --> 42:15.030
It's an easy question.

42:15.933 --> 42:18.299
Are you a man or are you a mouse?

42:21.372 --> 42:22.703
And your actions have told us

42:22.773 --> 42:25.799
that you have a great deal
of trouble being a mouse.

42:27.244 --> 42:29.109
It is the judgment of this court

42:29.213 --> 42:31.773
that you should be banished
from these walls forever.

42:32.449 --> 42:36.249
You shall be remanded into the
custody of Hovis, the Threadmaster,

42:36.320 --> 42:39.585
who will prepare you for your
descent into the dungeons of Dor,

42:39.657 --> 42:43.252
from which no mouse
and no light has ever escaped.

42:55.339 --> 42:57.500
- Shh!
- My baby!

42:57.641 --> 43:01.236
Quiet. Be quiet, my dear.
There's nothing to be done.

43:26.770 --> 43:28.203
Come with me.

43:36.647 --> 43:38.012
Stand there.

43:49.360 --> 43:50.418
Red?

43:50.728 --> 43:52.662
Ah, so they tell me.

43:55.032 --> 43:57.000
So you're the brave one.

43:58.102 --> 43:59.228
I guess.

43:59.336 --> 44:01.861
It's good. It'll carry well down there.

44:03.574 --> 44:05.201
Wear it proudly.

44:06.043 --> 44:07.567
There's no shame.

44:10.414 --> 44:11.711
It's time.

44:14.551 --> 44:17.884
It's all right.
They're too scared to come down here.

44:24.294 --> 44:25.556
In there?

44:25.929 --> 44:27.419
I'm afraid so.

44:29.266 --> 44:30.790
Courage, right?

44:30.901 --> 44:32.232
And truth.

44:32.803 --> 44:34.771
- And honor.
- Good.

44:34.872 --> 44:37.432
But especially courage.

44:49.253 --> 44:50.277
I'm ready.

44:50.387 --> 44:52.412
All right, then you need to...

44:55.459 --> 44:56.551
(EXCLAIMS)

45:09.139 --> 45:10.163
(GROANS)

45:30.294 --> 45:31.818
What? Whoa!

46:12.035 --> 46:14.333
(SNORING)

46:18.242 --> 46:20.073
(RATS CHATTERING)

46:28.018 --> 46:30.987
Hello? Hello?

46:32.189 --> 46:33.213
(GRUMBLES)

46:33.690 --> 46:34.714
Whoa!

46:37.394 --> 46:38.486
(WHISTLES)

46:38.562 --> 46:39.893
Lads, let's go, on the double!

46:39.997 --> 46:41.021
(EXCLAIMS)

46:43.734 --> 46:44.758
Who is that?

46:45.335 --> 46:46.666
Who goes there?

46:47.571 --> 46:48.833
Who is that?

46:48.906 --> 46:50.430
Despereaux Tilling.

46:50.541 --> 46:52.736
Are you a man or are you a mouse?

46:54.611 --> 46:57.239
I am a gentleman.

46:57.614 --> 46:59.081
(CHUCKLING) Oh.

46:59.516 --> 47:00.574
(RATS CLAMORING)

47:00.684 --> 47:02.242
- It's a mouse.
- I'm hungry.

47:02.352 --> 47:05.378
Shh! Quiet, lads. Patience.

47:06.723 --> 47:09.248
And what makes you a gentleman?

47:09.760 --> 47:11.022
A code...

47:11.094 --> 47:12.391
A code of honor.

47:12.462 --> 47:13.520
(LAUGHS)

47:13.597 --> 47:15.724
You're a strange little
mouse, aren't you?

47:15.799 --> 47:18.267
And where did you find
this code of honor?

47:18.368 --> 47:20.302
Well, in a legend.

47:20.404 --> 47:21.803
A legend that I read.

47:21.905 --> 47:24.635
Fine. Oh, tell me this legend of yours.

47:24.741 --> 47:26.971
I could do with a good story right now.

47:27.277 --> 47:28.608
Well,

47:28.712 --> 47:31.112
it's about a princess and a knight

47:32.282 --> 47:34.273
and his quest to save her honor.

47:34.751 --> 47:38.084
Ah. It was a princess
that took away my soup.

47:38.589 --> 47:40.079
She didn't take it.

47:40.157 --> 47:42.284
In fact, she misses it, too!

47:42.392 --> 47:43.484
(RATS MURMURING)

47:43.594 --> 47:45.721
How do you know all this, then?

47:45.796 --> 47:46.888
I've seen her.

47:47.231 --> 47:48.960
- Seen her?
- I've talked to her.

47:49.066 --> 47:51.500
- Talked to her?
- That's why they sent me down here.

47:51.602 --> 47:53.900
Mmm-hmm.
And what did this princess tell you

47:53.971 --> 47:55.632
when you had your little audience?

47:55.739 --> 47:57.138
(LAUGHING) Eh? Eh?

47:57.241 --> 48:00.005
Oh, you must be a royal mouse.
Is that it?

48:00.477 --> 48:04.004
She told me that
she missed the soup and the rain

48:04.748 --> 48:06.648
and, most of all, the sunlight.

48:07.351 --> 48:09.945
And that she just
wanted it all to come back again.

48:13.357 --> 48:14.949
Well, I don't want to
hear your little stories

48:15.025 --> 48:16.959
about princesses and sunshine.

48:17.928 --> 48:19.759
Go tell them to the rats!

48:19.963 --> 48:20.987
(GRUNTS)

48:21.465 --> 48:22.955
(RATS MURMURING)

48:26.436 --> 48:27.698
All right, boys, come on!

48:27.804 --> 48:29.362
(RATS SHOUTING)

48:41.852 --> 48:43.183
(CROWD CHEERING)

48:54.898 --> 48:55.956
(GRUNTING)

49:05.876 --> 49:06.900
(LAUGHING)

49:08.245 --> 49:09.542
Good crowd, isn't it, sir?

49:10.147 --> 49:12.172
Yes, it is, quite.

49:12.249 --> 49:14.376
CROWD: (CHANTING) Mouse! Mouse!
Mouse! Mouse!

49:21.358 --> 49:24.691
Ah, Roscuro! I'm glad you could make it.

49:24.761 --> 49:27.252
I thought you didn't like the arena.

49:27.364 --> 49:30.492
Huh? Oh! No, no.
It... It's an honor, sir.

49:31.168 --> 49:32.226
Oh!

49:32.336 --> 49:33.530
- BOTTICELLl: Good.
- Mmm.

49:33.704 --> 49:35.729
Well, enjoy.

49:36.173 --> 49:39.199
(STAMMERING) Oh, uh... Thank you.

49:39.276 --> 49:41.073
(CROWD CHEERING)

49:44.214 --> 49:46.182
Let the games begin!

49:54.725 --> 49:55.749
(ANIMAL SQUEALING)

49:59.529 --> 50:02.191
CROWD: (CHANTING) Mouse! Mouse! Mouse!

50:07.938 --> 50:09.303
(MEOWING)

50:09.473 --> 50:10.906
(CROWD CHEERING)

50:19.583 --> 50:20.880
(CROWD GROANING)

50:20.951 --> 50:21.975
RAT: Come on!

50:25.989 --> 50:27.286
(SNARLS)

50:27.424 --> 50:28.448
(MEOWS)

50:31.294 --> 50:32.886
(CROWD CHEERING)

50:35.732 --> 50:36.756
(SQUEALS)

51:03.693 --> 51:04.751
(SNARLS)

51:05.495 --> 51:06.519
Hold on!

51:12.869 --> 51:15.201
CROWD: (CHANTING) Eat! Eat! Eat!

51:20.477 --> 51:22.138
(RAT SHOUTING)

51:25.148 --> 51:26.172
ROSCURO: Wait!

51:26.516 --> 51:30.316
(STAMMERING) Can I have him?
Can I have this one? Please?

51:30.687 --> 51:32.655
(CROWD GRUMBLING)

51:33.957 --> 51:34.981
What?

51:35.392 --> 51:38.691
It's just that that one looks tasty.

51:38.862 --> 51:41.490
Well, this is progress.

51:41.565 --> 51:45.729
Perhaps we're starting
to leave the past behind us, eh?

51:45.836 --> 51:48.236
Enjoy, my friend.

51:48.338 --> 51:50.568
Don't leave a morsel.

51:50.674 --> 51:52.972
(STAMMERING) Oh, I won't.

51:53.844 --> 51:54.902
(SNAPS)

51:55.011 --> 51:56.035
Pull!

51:57.714 --> 51:58.738
(WHIMPERS)

51:58.915 --> 52:00.712
(CROWD GRUMBLING)

52:03.520 --> 52:05.351
(ALL CLAMORING)

52:12.362 --> 52:14.830
Come on, let's go, buster!

52:15.198 --> 52:18.190
That's it. That's it. You keep moving!

52:20.270 --> 52:23.103
(WHISPERING) It's okay. Keep walking.

52:23.373 --> 52:26.900
Come on, keep moving! Let's go, come on!

52:28.912 --> 52:30.345
(WHISPERING) It's right up there.

52:38.388 --> 52:40.049
- Huh?
- Keep walking.

52:47.697 --> 52:49.062
- Oh.
- See that?

52:50.133 --> 52:51.964
Light. Real light.

52:53.470 --> 52:55.938
It's mine, but you can share it.

52:56.606 --> 53:00.599
It isn't much, but there isn't much
anywhere since everything turned gray.

53:02.646 --> 53:04.273
You're not gonna eat me?

53:04.748 --> 53:06.943
No. I don't eat mice.

53:07.284 --> 53:08.717
Then what do you eat?

53:08.952 --> 53:10.078
Crumbs.

53:10.153 --> 53:11.484
When I can find them.

53:12.989 --> 53:15.321
So you are a gentleman.

53:18.094 --> 53:19.652
Tell me that story.

53:20.597 --> 53:22.064
About the Princess.

53:22.899 --> 53:24.764
Tell me what she looked like.

53:25.335 --> 53:27.132
Well, she was...

53:27.237 --> 53:28.499
Was she angry?

53:28.605 --> 53:29.799
No.

53:29.906 --> 53:31.567
No, not at all.

53:31.641 --> 53:34.576
Her heart was full of longing.

53:36.179 --> 53:37.771
What's longing?

53:39.683 --> 53:42.584
<i>NARRATOR: And that's</i>
<i>how a friendship is born.</i>

53:43.320 --> 53:47.313
<i>Over the next few weeks, he told Roscuro</i>
<i>everything he knew about loyalty</i>

53:47.424 --> 53:49.756
<i>and honor and
chivalry and courage.</i>

53:49.826 --> 53:53.159
<i>He told him about the Princess,</i>
<i>and where her longing came from.</i>

53:53.263 --> 53:57.097
<i>That she missed the rain and
the soup and even the rats.</i>

53:58.401 --> 53:59.493
Even the rats?

54:00.237 --> 54:04.401
<i>NARRATOR: He told him about their</i>
<i>code of honor, about his noble quest,</i>

54:04.841 --> 54:07.139
<i>about duty and loyalty.</i>

54:07.677 --> 54:10.771
<i>And there, in the
darkness of the cellar,</i>

54:10.847 --> 54:15.978
<i>two knights pledged devotion to a
princess who was trapped inside a castle.</i>

54:17.287 --> 54:19.812
<i>Trapped in a life full
of pain and longing.</i>

54:19.923 --> 54:21.823
<i>Even if no one could tell.</i>

54:25.962 --> 54:27.793
Your crown, ma'am.

54:29.032 --> 54:30.124
Oh.

54:31.167 --> 54:32.759
I don't want it today.

54:32.836 --> 54:34.633
But it's beautiful, ma'am.

54:34.971 --> 54:37.132
I know, but I don't want it.

54:37.207 --> 54:39.801
You look so pretty in it, ma'am.

54:39.876 --> 54:41.776
Like a princess.

54:42.045 --> 54:45.037
I know. I am the princess.

54:45.282 --> 54:46.840
Oh, I know, ma'am,

54:46.950 --> 54:51.148
but such a fine princess,
with a little, pretty, glittery...

54:51.221 --> 54:52.848
I don't want it!

54:52.956 --> 54:54.355
All right, Mig?

54:55.358 --> 54:56.985
Very well, ma'am.

54:57.627 --> 54:59.322
Please, take it away.

55:16.379 --> 55:17.403
MIG: Princess.

55:18.548 --> 55:20.038
Who's the princess?

55:20.684 --> 55:22.311
I'm a princess.

55:22.385 --> 55:24.319
I'm the princess.

55:26.156 --> 55:30.991
My comb, my hat, my gloves

55:32.028 --> 55:36.021
and my pretty powder

55:36.099 --> 55:38.659
on my pretty princess face.

55:38.835 --> 55:40.996
And what do you think you're doing?

55:41.071 --> 55:42.095
Ma'am!

55:42.205 --> 55:44.765
Where did you get all this?

55:44.874 --> 55:46.705
I just borrowed it, ma'am.

55:46.776 --> 55:47.902
Borrowed it?

55:48.244 --> 55:50.269
I was gonna put them all back.

55:50.413 --> 55:51.744
See that you do!

55:53.216 --> 55:56.083
And you can spend the whole week

55:56.186 --> 55:58.017
taking slop to the dungeon

55:58.088 --> 56:00.181
for your little escapade.

56:01.091 --> 56:02.422
"Princess"!

56:06.062 --> 56:08.963
God! She's the princess.

56:09.065 --> 56:10.123
(SCOFFS)

56:10.233 --> 56:14.863
And now I have to carry the sloppy,
gloppy, stinky stew

56:14.938 --> 56:17.634
down in the damp, dark, dingy...

56:19.876 --> 56:22.208
A person could get
lost forever down here.

56:24.314 --> 56:25.406
Oh!

56:25.482 --> 56:26.540
(SNORING)

56:27.083 --> 56:28.107
Din-din.

56:29.619 --> 56:30.643
Slop.

56:33.056 --> 56:36.719
No, don't stop! I said "slop"!

56:40.497 --> 56:41.589
(SIGHS)

56:41.664 --> 56:44.064
How am I supposed to eat this swill?

56:45.101 --> 56:48.434
Oh, stop that!
I don't have to be putting up with all this!

56:49.939 --> 56:51.634
I serve the Princess.

56:52.308 --> 56:53.673
(LAUGHING)

56:53.810 --> 56:56.472
Right. You serve the Princess.

56:56.579 --> 56:59.480
- That's a bit of a laugh, isn't it?
- I do.

56:59.582 --> 57:02.312
- I bring her tea and...
- Well, I don't want to hear it!

57:03.186 --> 57:05.154
Had me own little princess once.

57:05.688 --> 57:06.916
And now I don't.

57:07.357 --> 57:09.951
Oh. What, you had a princess?

57:11.861 --> 57:12.919
Yeah.

57:12.996 --> 57:15.294
Every dad's got a princess.

57:16.032 --> 57:18.091
<i>GREGORY: Till he stops being a dad,</i>
<i>of course.</i>

57:18.201 --> 57:19.463
(BABY COOING)

57:21.104 --> 57:23.937
Sorry. So, so, sorry!

57:25.642 --> 57:27.542
Oh, well, I've got a real one.

57:27.644 --> 57:30.704
And she's got a tiara and fancy robes,

57:30.814 --> 57:33.544
and she's got shiny bits
all over every frock in her closet.

57:33.650 --> 57:36.517
And I get to see her every single day.

57:37.620 --> 57:39.178
DESPEREAUX: What kind of a quest?

57:39.289 --> 57:40.313
Uh...

57:41.124 --> 57:42.887
To right a terrible wrong.

57:43.359 --> 57:45.327
But who did you wrong?

57:48.198 --> 57:49.222
Okay.

57:50.800 --> 57:53.496
Do you remember when
they banished the rats?

57:54.037 --> 57:55.698
- Sure. Yes.
- Okay.

57:56.539 --> 57:58.507
Well, it wasn't all
the rats they banished.

57:58.575 --> 58:03.012
I mean, they did, but it was
all because of one particular rat

58:03.847 --> 58:05.371
in particular.

58:05.515 --> 58:06.539
Oh.

58:07.817 --> 58:08.841
Mmm-hmm.

58:08.918 --> 58:10.647
If I could just tell her I'm sorry,

58:10.720 --> 58:15.054
that I'm, you know, I'm really sorry.

58:15.158 --> 58:17.854
And that I didn't mean
for any of this to happen.

58:17.927 --> 58:19.861
If she could just hear me say it,

58:19.929 --> 58:22.397
you know, just... Just hear my voice,

58:22.499 --> 58:25.730
(STAMMERING) she would
know how much I meant it.

58:27.570 --> 58:29.367
That is a very noble quest.

58:44.787 --> 58:47.187
ROSCURO: (STAMMERING) Your Highness?

58:50.126 --> 58:52.026
Your Highness?

58:53.129 --> 58:54.562
Is that you?

58:54.864 --> 58:56.229
My little mouse?

58:56.900 --> 58:58.800
Oh, I'm not a mouse. I...

58:59.269 --> 59:00.702
(STAMMERING) I'm a...

59:02.205 --> 59:03.229
Oh.

59:03.740 --> 59:04.866
I forgot.

59:05.141 --> 59:07.405
You're my little gentleman, aren't you?

59:10.480 --> 59:12.471
Have you come to tell me
how the story ends?

59:12.582 --> 59:14.277
Did you finish your quest?

59:15.485 --> 59:16.952
Where are you?

59:18.121 --> 59:20.089
I have come to apologize.

59:20.723 --> 59:23.248
Oh, you are noble, remember?

59:24.093 --> 59:26.254
You have nothing to be sorry about.

59:27.897 --> 59:29.330
Oh, but I am.

59:32.402 --> 59:33.835
I am sorry.

59:36.806 --> 59:38.740
(GASPING) I know you.

59:38.808 --> 59:41.299
- No, no.
- Oh, no!

59:41.411 --> 59:43.174
No! Please, please listen. Please.

59:43.279 --> 59:44.644
- A rat!
- Please. I just want to tell you.

59:44.747 --> 59:46.339
(SCREAMING) Someone, please!

59:46.449 --> 59:47.643
Listen. It's okay.

59:47.750 --> 59:50.150
Get it off me! There's a rat in my room!

59:50.486 --> 59:52.249
Please get him off!

59:52.322 --> 59:54.586
(SCREAMING)

59:57.994 --> 59:59.018
What?

01:00:00.663 --> 01:00:01.687
(PRINCESS PEA SHRIEKING)

01:00:04.867 --> 01:00:05.925
Rat!

01:00:06.469 --> 01:00:08.266
(PRINCESS PEA SHRIEKING)

01:00:08.371 --> 01:00:09.463
Oh!

01:00:10.773 --> 01:00:12.764
PRINCESS PEA: It's a rat!

01:00:19.849 --> 01:00:21.373
GUARD 1: Quick, rush him!

01:00:21.484 --> 01:00:22.542
GUARD 2: Get him!

01:00:22.652 --> 01:00:24.017
GUARD 3: Filthy rodent!

01:00:30.560 --> 01:00:31.618
Uh-oh.

01:00:32.996 --> 01:00:34.020
Oh!

01:00:39.235 --> 01:00:40.793
GUARD: Where'd he go?

01:00:48.878 --> 01:00:49.902
(GRUNTING)

01:00:51.881 --> 01:00:53.314
(PANTING)

01:01:21.744 --> 01:01:25.407
<i>NARRATOR: What would you do</i>
<i>if your own name was a bad word?</i>

01:01:27.550 --> 01:01:31.145
<i>If John or Beth or
Bill was an insult.</i>

01:01:32.689 --> 01:01:36.147
<i>Well, that's how Roscuro</i>
<i>came to feel about who he was.</i>

01:01:38.227 --> 01:01:42.220
<i>When your heart breaks,</i>
<i>it can grow back crooked.</i>

01:01:43.232 --> 01:01:46.998
<i>It grows back twisted
and gnarled and hard.</i>

01:01:49.338 --> 01:01:52.705
<i>Even as he changed,</i>
<i>Roscuro still had longing.</i>

01:01:53.743 --> 01:01:58.112
<i>But now he just longed for someone
whose heart was as hardened as his was.</i>

01:01:59.115 --> 01:02:04.678
Pretty princess.
Pretty, pretty princess pie.

01:02:05.755 --> 01:02:07.780
What a pretty princess!

01:02:09.425 --> 01:02:10.756
My gloves.

01:02:11.627 --> 01:02:12.855
My comb.

01:02:14.130 --> 01:02:16.860
My jewel-y, girly hat,

01:02:17.266 --> 01:02:21.600
all sitting on my princess head.

01:02:24.974 --> 01:02:30.310
Who's the pretty princess pumpkin pie?

01:02:33.282 --> 01:02:34.306
You are.

01:02:34.650 --> 01:02:37.278
Right. I am.

01:02:37.553 --> 01:02:41.284
You are. And you should be
dressed in those clothes.

01:02:41.958 --> 01:02:44.791
Quite right. I should.

01:02:44.994 --> 01:02:47.963
Mmm-hmm.
And you should lounge in that bed.

01:02:48.064 --> 01:02:49.326
Lounging.

01:02:49.432 --> 01:02:53.334
Lounging round, yes, the whole day!

01:02:53.736 --> 01:02:56.227
And you should be wearing that crown.

01:02:57.073 --> 01:02:58.665
I should be wearing a frown?

01:02:58.775 --> 01:03:02.472
No. No, no, no. Not a frown. A crown.

01:03:02.578 --> 01:03:05.775
Wow! Can't hear me own self think.

01:03:08.451 --> 01:03:09.679
- Ah!
- Shh!

01:03:09.786 --> 01:03:11.811
- Ah!
- Shh!

01:03:12.455 --> 01:03:13.513
Shh!

01:03:13.623 --> 01:03:15.352
- Ah!
- Shh!

01:03:17.126 --> 01:03:18.593
Who are you?

01:03:18.661 --> 01:03:20.253
I'm here to help you.

01:03:20.329 --> 01:03:22.923
I can't be caught with
a real rat in my bunk.

01:03:23.432 --> 01:03:25.093
I don't think so.

01:03:25.168 --> 01:03:26.192
(INHALES)

01:03:27.203 --> 01:03:29.763
And what if they find you
with a painting of the Princess?

01:03:29.839 --> 01:03:31.830
You think that's as bad as a rat?

01:03:32.608 --> 01:03:34.269
I want the same thing you do.

01:03:43.686 --> 01:03:45.176
(CLANKING)

01:03:46.189 --> 01:03:47.213
<i>Allo?</i>

01:03:49.659 --> 01:03:52.321
(BOTH EXCLAIMING)

01:03:52.395 --> 01:03:53.453
What are you doing?

01:03:53.696 --> 01:03:54.720
Uh...

01:03:55.665 --> 01:03:57.565
I need it for a baby.

01:03:59.468 --> 01:04:01.299
No, not a baby!

01:04:01.804 --> 01:04:02.828
For milady.

01:04:02.972 --> 01:04:05.736
(STAMMERING) I mean milady.

01:04:06.409 --> 01:04:07.501
Yes.

01:04:08.010 --> 01:04:09.238
To chop apples.

01:04:09.345 --> 01:04:10.369
Mmm.

01:04:10.479 --> 01:04:11.912
She'd like some apples.

01:04:14.550 --> 01:04:15.710
Now turn and leave.

01:04:15.818 --> 01:04:17.718
Now turn and leave.

01:04:20.223 --> 01:04:23.351
No, no! Just turn and leave.

01:04:23.559 --> 01:04:25.322
Oh, right. Sorry.

01:04:25.895 --> 01:04:26.919
Sorry. Bye.

01:04:27.029 --> 01:04:30.328
Oh, I can't hear you,
see, because deaf, but...

01:04:30.433 --> 01:04:31.491
A bit deaf.

01:04:34.670 --> 01:04:37.195
<i>NARRATOR: You know,
hurt is a funny thing.</i>

01:04:37.273 --> 01:04:41.869
<i>The same thing that makes one person angry</i>
<i>can put another person into grief.</i>

01:04:41.944 --> 01:04:44.674
Here, take care of me little princess.

01:04:44.947 --> 01:04:46.539
I can't no more.

01:04:46.782 --> 01:04:49.342
Oh, I will. Don't worry.

01:04:50.286 --> 01:04:51.344
(BABY COOING)

01:04:51.420 --> 01:04:52.512
I'm sorry.

01:04:53.222 --> 01:04:56.214
Sorry. So, so sorry!

01:04:59.395 --> 01:05:02.523
<i>NARRATOR: Gregory always said</i>
<i>that she had too much heart.</i>

01:05:02.598 --> 01:05:06.364
<i>And that's why they had to put</i>
<i>some of it on the outside.</i>

01:05:06.435 --> 01:05:07.868
<i>But let's face it.</i>

01:05:07.937 --> 01:05:10.599
<i>It's hard to see
something on your back.</i>

01:05:10.706 --> 01:05:14.802
<i>In fact, you can have a good heart</i>
<i>and not even know it.</i>

01:05:14.944 --> 01:05:16.707
You can do this. You know you can.

01:05:17.146 --> 01:05:18.374
I know I can.

01:05:18.447 --> 01:05:23.077
She belongs in the dungeon,
and you belong in the palace, like a princess.

01:05:24.620 --> 01:05:25.814
(CLATTERING)

01:05:28.758 --> 01:05:29.918
What are you doing?

01:05:31.227 --> 01:05:32.387
I'm cleaning, ma'am.

01:05:32.461 --> 01:05:33.485
(GROANS)

01:05:33.896 --> 01:05:35.227
With rope?

01:05:35.398 --> 01:05:36.422
It helps, ma'am.

01:05:36.499 --> 01:05:38.399
Well, stop it. You look ridiculous.

01:05:41.003 --> 01:05:42.129
Sorry, ma'am?

01:05:42.238 --> 01:05:44.798
I said you look ridiculous.

01:05:44.907 --> 01:05:48.172
<i>(ECHOING) Ridiculous,</i>
<i>ridiculous, ridiculous.</i>

01:05:50.079 --> 01:05:51.740
- You can't do this, Mig.
- Gor.

01:05:51.981 --> 01:05:53.608
Seems I am, ma'am.

01:05:53.683 --> 01:05:55.150
You'll get in a terrible
amount of trouble.

01:05:55.251 --> 01:05:57.242
Don't listen. You're the princess now.

01:05:57.320 --> 01:05:58.810
I'm the princess now.

01:05:58.921 --> 01:06:00.616
And you belong in the palace.

01:06:00.690 --> 01:06:02.317
I belong in the palace.

01:06:02.425 --> 01:06:03.483
And she belongs in...

01:06:03.592 --> 01:06:05.583
PRINCESS PEA: No! You can't do this!

01:06:05.661 --> 01:06:08.926
Help! Help! Someone help me!

01:06:08.998 --> 01:06:10.966
Help! Help!

01:06:11.767 --> 01:06:14.292
(FAINTLY) Help! Help!

01:06:19.976 --> 01:06:22.035
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

01:06:23.346 --> 01:06:25.177
PRINCESS PEA: Help! Help!

01:06:27.149 --> 01:06:28.616
Help!

01:06:29.518 --> 01:06:31.349
MIG: I'm in here!

01:06:33.322 --> 01:06:34.812
Help!

01:06:35.157 --> 01:06:37.022
You filthy, stinking rat!

01:06:38.160 --> 01:06:39.627
You tricked me!

01:06:39.895 --> 01:06:41.795
(RATS CLAMORING)

01:06:42.565 --> 01:06:43.657
RAT 1: Here's the spot, rats!

01:06:43.733 --> 01:06:45.132
SMUDGE: What's Roscuro brought us, then?

01:06:45.201 --> 01:06:46.634
RAT 2: Hungry! Yum! Hungry now!

01:06:46.702 --> 01:06:48.533
Not yet, lads.
No, no, you've got to wait.

01:06:48.637 --> 01:06:50.036
It's nowhere near dinnertime.

01:06:50.139 --> 01:06:52.164
Oh, come on, Smudge, I'm starving.

01:06:52.241 --> 01:06:53.902
(PRINCESS PEA SOBBING)

01:06:57.546 --> 01:06:59.878
RAT 1: Something special
for dinner tonight.

01:07:00.249 --> 01:07:01.739
RAT 3: Smells delicious!

01:07:03.853 --> 01:07:06.981
RAT 2: Smells human to me. A young one.
RAT 3: And not just any human.

01:07:07.056 --> 01:07:09.081
RAT 2: Let's have a look.
RAT 3: It's the Princess!

01:07:09.191 --> 01:07:11.022
SMUDGE: Oi, you'll wait
for your dinner like everyone else.

01:07:11.093 --> 01:07:12.151
RAT 2: Come on, Smudge,
give us a little look.

01:07:12.228 --> 01:07:13.320
SMUDGE: No, no, no!

01:07:13.396 --> 01:07:15.864
SMUDGE: Boss doesn't want her getting
nervous. Spoils the meat, doesn't it?

01:07:18.601 --> 01:07:19.659
(CRYING)

01:07:20.603 --> 01:07:22.036
DESPEREAUX: Milady!

01:07:22.405 --> 01:07:24.339
Psst! Milady!

01:07:25.007 --> 01:07:28.033
Oh, my little mouse! It's you.

01:07:28.277 --> 01:07:30.575
I will deliver you from this evil, ma'am.

01:07:30.679 --> 01:07:32.738
Oh, no. Just go find my father.

01:07:33.416 --> 01:07:35.213
Take this chain from around my neck.

01:07:35.284 --> 01:07:37.115
To show him you are honest and truthful.

01:07:37.219 --> 01:07:40.586
Oh, I am!
Honest and truthful and loyal and...

01:07:40.689 --> 01:07:41.781
I know.

01:07:41.891 --> 01:07:42.949
But hurry.

01:07:43.059 --> 01:07:44.526
Here. Take it.

01:07:44.794 --> 01:07:46.352
There isn't much time.

01:07:55.271 --> 01:07:56.295
(GRUNTS)

01:08:55.464 --> 01:08:56.488
Whoa!

01:08:59.801 --> 01:09:00.826
Ha-ha!

01:09:07.176 --> 01:09:08.643
Oh, oh!

01:09:17.319 --> 01:09:18.911
(LUTE PLAYING)

01:09:28.464 --> 01:09:29.590
(CROWD CHEERING)

01:09:34.703 --> 01:09:36.330
RAT 1: Hey, did you get some?
RAT 2: Oh, yeah.

01:09:36.438 --> 01:09:37.769
Here you are, sir.

01:09:37.840 --> 01:09:38.932
Fresh worms.

01:09:39.008 --> 01:09:40.532
Oh, um...

01:09:41.477 --> 01:09:42.501
Thank you.

01:09:47.616 --> 01:09:50.107
Well done, Roscuro!

01:09:50.685 --> 01:09:51.983
You hear that?

01:09:52.054 --> 01:09:54.318
That's all because of you.

01:09:54.823 --> 01:09:59.123
Come, my friend. Look at your handiwork.

01:09:59.628 --> 01:10:01.118
(CROWD CHEERING)

01:10:17.379 --> 01:10:18.846
(PLAYING LUTE)

01:10:23.219 --> 01:10:26.518
DESPEREAUX: King! King!
Sire, your daughter is in danger!

01:10:26.589 --> 01:10:28.079
Sire, up here!

01:10:28.924 --> 01:10:31.825
Your Highness! Please, sir!

01:10:34.330 --> 01:10:35.592
Oh, come on.

01:10:36.665 --> 01:10:37.689
Oh!

01:10:42.671 --> 01:10:43.695
Hey, Sire!

01:10:44.773 --> 01:10:46.365
Your Highness!

01:10:46.609 --> 01:10:48.600
Look, Your Highness! Look!

01:10:48.711 --> 01:10:50.008
Hello, Mr. King!

01:10:50.546 --> 01:10:51.570
Hey, hello!

01:10:51.680 --> 01:10:52.704
Whoa!

01:10:54.383 --> 01:10:56.078
Down here! Hello! Down here!

01:10:56.185 --> 01:10:57.777
Listen, your daughter is in danger!

01:10:57.886 --> 01:10:59.217
She's in a dungeon!

01:10:59.288 --> 01:11:00.721
You're the only one who can help!

01:11:00.789 --> 01:11:02.450
She sent me to get you!

01:11:02.558 --> 01:11:03.752
Sir, please! Sir...

01:11:03.859 --> 01:11:05.383
Ooh! Sire!

01:11:05.461 --> 01:11:06.860
Your Highness!

01:11:06.929 --> 01:11:11.263
Look down here! Whoa!

01:11:12.801 --> 01:11:13.859
(GRUMBLES)

01:11:20.709 --> 01:11:21.801
(EXCLAIMS)

01:11:21.910 --> 01:11:23.935
Dad? Dad, listen. You've got to help me.

01:11:24.046 --> 01:11:25.980
(STUTTERING) But you're dead!

01:11:26.081 --> 01:11:27.742
No. No, I'm not. I'm not dead!

01:11:27.816 --> 01:11:30.910
Now, listen. The Princess is in danger.
She's locked in the dungeon.

01:11:30.986 --> 01:11:34.444
Oh, my golly, you're dead.

01:11:35.090 --> 01:11:37.149
Dad! Dad, I'm not dead!

01:11:37.259 --> 01:11:40.422
Dad, I'm not dead!
Oh, Dad, wake up, please!

01:11:44.166 --> 01:11:45.258
(EXCLAIMING)

01:11:45.334 --> 01:11:46.733
Furlough, listen. You've gotta help me.

01:11:46.802 --> 01:11:48.326
(STUTTERING) You're...

01:11:48.437 --> 01:11:49.995
No. No, I'm not dead.

01:11:50.105 --> 01:11:52.801
Listen, the Princess is in danger.
She's locked in the cellar.

01:11:52.908 --> 01:11:56.139
Oh, my God, you're dead!

01:11:56.245 --> 01:11:57.269
No!

01:11:57.746 --> 01:11:58.804
Whoo!

01:11:58.914 --> 01:12:00.279
DESPEREAUX: Guys? Listen.

01:12:00.616 --> 01:12:02.106
Okay, look. Now, I'm not dead.

01:12:02.184 --> 01:12:04.948
The Princess is in danger,
and she's down in the dungeon

01:12:05.020 --> 01:12:07.648
and you've gotta... You've gotta help me!

01:12:07.756 --> 01:12:09.121
Somebody?

01:12:21.670 --> 01:12:22.694
Whoa!

01:12:22.805 --> 01:12:24.705
(BELL TOLLING)

01:12:27.476 --> 01:12:28.500
Whoa!

01:12:36.618 --> 01:12:37.642
Whoa!

01:12:46.795 --> 01:12:47.819
Hmm.

01:12:55.704 --> 01:12:57.296
Oh!

01:12:59.375 --> 01:13:00.433
Oh!

01:13:01.043 --> 01:13:02.271
Oh, ho, ho!

01:13:09.685 --> 01:13:10.709
Ah!

01:13:13.489 --> 01:13:14.820
Whoa!

01:13:17.626 --> 01:13:18.650
(SHOUTS)

01:13:19.962 --> 01:13:21.054
Oh, I must have been...

01:13:26.702 --> 01:13:27.726
Enough!

01:13:32.975 --> 01:13:33.999
Ah-ha!

01:13:35.077 --> 01:13:36.840
(WATER BOILING)

01:13:37.413 --> 01:13:38.505
Ah!

01:13:43.519 --> 01:13:44.543
(SNIFFING)

01:13:51.393 --> 01:13:52.417
(BARKS)

01:14:15.717 --> 01:14:16.741
(BARKS)

01:14:22.324 --> 01:14:23.382
(HUMMING)

01:14:24.560 --> 01:14:25.584
<i>Voilà!</i>

01:14:33.735 --> 01:14:36.465
Look at you! You are still brewing tea.

01:14:37.239 --> 01:14:39.935
If you want to make a statement,
what do I say?

01:14:40.342 --> 01:14:41.639
Make it a good one!

01:14:43.011 --> 01:14:45.309
Ah, it's so great to see you!

01:14:45.414 --> 01:14:46.676
BOLDO: Fantastic!

01:14:49.284 --> 01:14:51.013
- Ah.
- Marjoram?

01:14:51.119 --> 01:14:52.347
Mmm-hmm. Love it. Perfect.

01:14:52.454 --> 01:14:54.081
- Ah! <i>Superbe!</i>
<i>- Bellissima!</i>

01:14:56.358 --> 01:14:58.656
Basil, will you look at that?

01:14:59.962 --> 01:15:00.986
Oh!

01:15:01.697 --> 01:15:03.824
Look up there!
Marge, come and have a look at this!

01:15:03.932 --> 01:15:04.956
Oh, my!

01:15:06.702 --> 01:15:07.760
(SNIFFING)

01:15:10.973 --> 01:15:11.997
Mmm!

01:15:16.378 --> 01:15:17.504
Cauliflower?

01:15:17.613 --> 01:15:19.274
Perfect. Perfect, yes, it's about time.

01:15:19.348 --> 01:15:20.610
<i>Basilico.</i>

01:15:21.183 --> 01:15:22.377
Eh, some celery?

01:15:23.051 --> 01:15:24.211
Hey, hello!

01:15:24.319 --> 01:15:25.877
Good, celery. Parsley, maybe.

01:15:26.355 --> 01:15:28.186
- DESPEREAUX: The Princess is in danger!
- No, no, no.

01:15:28.290 --> 01:15:30.019
- Garlic! Should I use the garlic?
- Look down here!

01:15:30.125 --> 01:15:32.525
- I mean not too much, but just a little bit.
- Oh, no, no, no, of course.

01:15:32.628 --> 01:15:34.027
- It is fantastic!
- Yes.

01:15:34.129 --> 01:15:35.153
<i>Bellissima!</i>

01:15:35.230 --> 01:15:37.061
Brav-ow!

01:15:37.399 --> 01:15:38.457
Oh.

01:15:38.634 --> 01:15:40.727
The Princess is in danger!

01:15:40.836 --> 01:15:41.894
Ooh!

01:15:44.172 --> 01:15:46.572
You are a cute little mouse.

01:15:47.409 --> 01:15:49.036
Would you like some soup?

01:15:49.144 --> 01:15:50.202
No, I don't want...

01:15:50.312 --> 01:15:52.507
The Princess is in danger!

01:15:52.581 --> 01:15:54.173
And a talking mouse, too.

01:15:54.249 --> 01:15:55.682
Listen, you've gotta help me.

01:15:55.751 --> 01:15:57.343
Perhaps a little cheese?

01:15:57.419 --> 01:15:59.683
No, I don't want any cheese!

01:15:59.755 --> 01:16:02.315
The Princess! She's in danger!

01:16:02.391 --> 01:16:04.052
She's locked in the dungeon!

01:16:04.159 --> 01:16:05.217
(GASPS)

01:16:05.327 --> 01:16:06.351
In the dungeon!

01:16:06.428 --> 01:16:08.760
Oh, don't be silly, my little mouse.

01:16:08.864 --> 01:16:10.422
Everything is fine!

01:16:10.532 --> 01:16:13.660
The Princess is perfectly
safe up in her...

01:16:13.769 --> 01:16:14.827
(GASPS)

01:16:21.777 --> 01:16:24.371
(VILLAGERS CHATTERING EXCITEDLY)

01:16:28.717 --> 01:16:29.741
Oh, my.

01:16:30.052 --> 01:16:31.542
Boldo!

01:16:31.720 --> 01:16:33.244
Look! It's...

01:16:34.623 --> 01:16:35.681
Boldo.

01:16:36.458 --> 01:16:37.720
Where are you?

01:16:38.860 --> 01:16:41.124
Charge!

01:16:42.097 --> 01:16:43.189
Tell me again.

01:16:43.265 --> 01:16:44.289
- Chivalry!
- Mmm.

01:16:44.399 --> 01:16:45.457
- Bravery!
- Mmm-hmm.

01:16:45.567 --> 01:16:46.591
Honor!

01:16:46.702 --> 01:16:50.638
Chivalry! Bravery! Honor!

01:16:50.906 --> 01:16:52.100
I love it!

01:16:52.207 --> 01:16:55.267
Oh, it feels so good to
be out of the kitchen!

01:16:55.711 --> 01:16:57.269
Let's go!

01:16:57.779 --> 01:16:59.713
Into the breach!

01:17:01.083 --> 01:17:02.107
Down there.

01:17:02.217 --> 01:17:03.582
<i>Andiamo!</i>

01:17:05.087 --> 01:17:06.145
Whoa!

01:17:07.956 --> 01:17:09.048
Ha-ha!

01:17:09.958 --> 01:17:10.982
(GASPS)

01:17:15.564 --> 01:17:16.826
Where did she go?

01:17:16.932 --> 01:17:18.229
(CROWD CHEERING)

01:17:19.735 --> 01:17:21.100
BOTTICELLl: My friends!

01:17:21.503 --> 01:17:24.267
My friends, there are rats,

01:17:24.339 --> 01:17:29.936
and then there are rats!

01:17:31.480 --> 01:17:34.608
And I would like a huge round of applause

01:17:34.683 --> 01:17:37.117
for our good friend here

01:17:37.185 --> 01:17:42.020
for delivering us our princess!

01:17:44.793 --> 01:17:45.987
Come on, let's go!

01:17:47.429 --> 01:17:50.694
Oi! Hang on! Where you going? Help!

01:17:53.702 --> 01:17:54.760
Hurry!

01:17:56.438 --> 01:17:57.462
Look at that!

01:17:57.806 --> 01:17:59.296
Let's get him, boys.

01:18:09.017 --> 01:18:10.848
Ow! Ow, ow, ow!

01:18:12.688 --> 01:18:13.712
Keep going! Keep going!

01:18:13.822 --> 01:18:15.722
Please! Oh, no, get off of me!

01:18:20.529 --> 01:18:21.553
Nice shot!

01:18:24.332 --> 01:18:25.356
That's my onion!

01:18:29.037 --> 01:18:30.402
(DESPEREAUX SCREAMING)

01:18:46.988 --> 01:18:48.478
MIG: Hello?

01:18:48.590 --> 01:18:49.648
Help!

01:18:50.692 --> 01:18:52.683
Help!

01:18:52.761 --> 01:18:54.160
Can anybody hear me?

01:18:56.231 --> 01:18:57.755
Help!

01:18:58.834 --> 01:19:00.734
I'm in here!

01:19:01.737 --> 01:19:02.829
(GASPING)

01:19:02.904 --> 01:19:04.269
I'm in here!

01:19:05.107 --> 01:19:06.574
I'm in here!

01:19:06.675 --> 01:19:07.699
(SOBBING)

01:19:10.746 --> 01:19:11.770
(GREGORY GASPS)

01:19:13.448 --> 01:19:14.506
(KEYS CLATTER)

01:19:15.117 --> 01:19:16.175
Oh, gor!

01:19:16.952 --> 01:19:18.579
What took you so long?

01:19:18.687 --> 01:19:22.248
I've been screaming in here
for over two hours.

01:19:24.059 --> 01:19:26.459
My little princess.

01:19:30.432 --> 01:19:31.524
Rain.

01:19:31.600 --> 01:19:32.624
Yes.

01:19:41.076 --> 01:19:42.771
Papa! Papa, look!

01:19:43.078 --> 01:19:44.102
Up there!

01:19:44.446 --> 01:19:45.640
(ALL GASPING)

01:19:46.148 --> 01:19:47.206
The sun!

01:19:54.990 --> 01:19:56.423
(GROANING)

01:20:03.465 --> 01:20:05.228
Go on, Despereaux.

01:20:09.971 --> 01:20:11.336
(ALL CLAMORING)

01:20:13.642 --> 01:20:18.272
Wait! Wait just a moment! Patience!

01:20:19.114 --> 01:20:20.172
(GASPS)

01:20:21.082 --> 01:20:24.677
Not just yet.

01:20:27.322 --> 01:20:28.789
(CROWD CHEERING)

01:20:31.593 --> 01:20:36.826
The honor is all yours, my friend.

01:20:40.702 --> 01:20:43.603
CROWD: (CHANTING) Eat! Eat! Eat!

01:20:43.872 --> 01:20:46.306
Eat! Eat! Eat!

01:20:52.514 --> 01:20:55.347
<i>NARRATOR: Okay, remember</i>
<i>when we said that grief</i>

01:20:55.450 --> 01:20:58.044
<i>was the strongest thing
a person could feel?</i>

01:20:58.153 --> 01:20:59.643
<i>Well, it isn't.</i>

01:21:00.488 --> 01:21:01.978
<i>It's forgiveness.</i>

01:21:02.524 --> 01:21:06.483
<i>Because a single act of
forgiveness can change everything.</i>

01:21:07.729 --> 01:21:08.787
No.

01:21:09.231 --> 01:21:10.289
What?

01:21:10.365 --> 01:21:11.389
No.

01:21:11.900 --> 01:21:14.027
You worthless little...

01:21:14.236 --> 01:21:16.670
CROWD: Eat! Eat! Eat!

01:21:20.809 --> 01:21:21.833
(SCREAMING)

01:21:33.154 --> 01:21:34.917
(SNARLING)

01:21:38.326 --> 01:21:39.350
Help!

01:21:46.434 --> 01:21:48.766
(SNARLING)

01:21:49.738 --> 01:21:51.603
(ALL SCREAMING)

01:21:53.675 --> 01:21:55.506
Who let him out?

01:22:02.684 --> 01:22:03.708
Hey, you!

01:22:03.919 --> 01:22:04.943
It's that mouse!

01:22:10.692 --> 01:22:11.716
Get him!

01:22:56.237 --> 01:23:00.731
Ah, if it isn't our brave little knight.

01:23:02.143 --> 01:23:04.134
- I wonder.
- No!

01:23:04.245 --> 01:23:07.146
Should I finish you off myself

01:23:07.248 --> 01:23:10.581
or turn you into cat food?

01:23:20.195 --> 01:23:23.460
Here, kitty, kitty, kitty.

01:23:26.167 --> 01:23:30.194
What is that?

01:23:52.227 --> 01:23:54.161
(SCREAMING)

01:24:00.902 --> 01:24:02.335
(CAT GROWLING)

01:24:03.505 --> 01:24:06.235
Please. Nice kitty?

01:24:08.043 --> 01:24:09.374
No, no, no, no!

01:24:13.982 --> 01:24:15.006
(CAT SNARLING)

01:24:19.854 --> 01:24:20.912
Hmm?

01:24:27.062 --> 01:24:29.189
(ALL EXCLAIMING IN PAIN)

01:24:56.424 --> 01:24:58.915
Thank you, my good gentleman.

01:24:59.661 --> 01:25:00.719
(GASPS)

01:25:10.638 --> 01:25:12.265
I am sorry.

01:25:15.276 --> 01:25:17.676
I'm the one who should be sorry.

01:25:20.782 --> 01:25:25.583
I'm so, so sorry.
You've no idea how sorry I am.

01:25:26.621 --> 01:25:27.986
That's all right.

01:25:32.093 --> 01:25:34.118
(TOWNSPEOPLE CHEERING)

01:25:34.796 --> 01:25:36.354
I'm so sorry.

01:25:43.271 --> 01:25:45.330
<i>NARRATOR:
So, you could call all of this</i>

01:25:45.440 --> 01:25:47.874
<i>a big misunderstanding
if you wanted to.</i>

01:25:47.976 --> 01:25:51.275
<i>A king was hurt, so he hurt a rat.</i>

01:25:51.346 --> 01:25:54.179
<i>And a rat was hurt,
so he hurt a princess.</i>

01:25:55.216 --> 01:25:58.344
<i>And a princess was hurt,</i>
<i>so she hurt a servant girl,</i>

01:25:58.453 --> 01:26:00.944
<i>without even meaning to do it.</i>

01:26:01.022 --> 01:26:03.957
<i>And that servant had been</i>
<i>hurting for so long,</i>

01:26:04.025 --> 01:26:07.119
<i>that almost nothing</i>
<i>could make her feel better.</i>

01:26:08.329 --> 01:26:13.028
<i>But was it a mistake</i>
<i>or was it just good luck?</i>

01:26:13.535 --> 01:26:16.163
<i>Because the servant girl</i>
<i>went back to her farm.</i>

01:26:16.237 --> 01:26:18.797
<i>And the jailer finally
found his princess.</i>

01:26:18.873 --> 01:26:22.001
<i>And the King found something</i>
<i>stronger than grief.</i>

01:26:22.076 --> 01:26:24.704
<i>And the mice finally
got rid of their fear.</i>

01:26:27.348 --> 01:26:31.148
<i>And the people of Dor</i>
<i>lived side by side with their rats.</i>

01:26:32.153 --> 01:26:33.484
<i>All except one.</i>

01:26:33.555 --> 01:26:35.147
<i>Who went back to sea</i>

01:26:35.223 --> 01:26:37.521
<i>and felt a cool
breeze each morning</i>

01:26:37.592 --> 01:26:40.755
<i>and the sun in his
face every afternoon.</i>

01:26:40.862 --> 01:26:45.162
<i>And we'd tell you that they all
lived happily ever after, but...</i>

01:26:45.233 --> 01:26:46.257
Whoa!

01:26:46.935 --> 01:26:48.232
<i>NARRATOR: what fun is that?</i>

01:26:48.369 --> 01:26:49.393
Whoa!

